{
  "text": "We applied the minimal method to Comparing the results with Figure 2(a) , the deterministic CA's diagram is diffusive only for a short period of time, and it settles into a static state. On the other hand, the stochastic CA's diagram shows diffusive behavior for a long time. When K is small, the diffusion width is small. The width increases monotonically as K tends to 0.5. These are consistent with the results by [CITATION_1] . ",
